de.iabg.mode
Interface MaterialReader

All Known Implementing Classes:
NastranDirectMatrixReader
public interface MaterialReader

This interface declares basic functionality for parsing a file containing material data, namely mass and stiffness matrices. In general, the user should call readFile() so that the parser reads and internally stores the data of the file. The data can then be safely parsed and extracted without having to stream file data multiple times.

Version:
September 11, 2008

Method Detail

importMassMatrices

void importMassMatrices(MassMatrixMap massMatrices)
Clears the given mass matrices and replaces them with the data parsed from the internally stored file. This method should be called after readFile(), otherwise no data will be saved.

Parameters:
massMatrices - the MassMatrixMap where the data will be stored

readFile

void readFile()
              throws java.io.IOException
Internally saves the data from the file for later use. The format of the lines may be altered as required to more easily parse the file.

Throws:
java.io.IOException - if the file could not be read
